OL,5,CCup ` study
OL,7,FParticipants were also between 22% and
OL,8,F33% more likely to place a bet during
OL,9,Fmatches that included televised
OL,10,Fgambling ads.
OL,12,FThe study's authors said that while
OL,13,Fparticipants reported no personal
OL,14,Fhistory of gambling problems, men and
OL,15,Findividuals aged 18 to 44 were known
OL,16,Fto disproportionately make up the
OL,17,Flargest group of sports gamblers in
OL,18,Fthe UK, and were also at the greatest
OL,19,Frisk of gambling-related harm.
