OL,5,CCup ` study
OL,7,F"Despite the scale of this issue,
OL,8,Fadvertising rules are not being
OL,9,Fstrengthened. Tighter regulation of
OL,10,Fgambling advertising during live sport
OL,11,Fmay be needed, particularly ahead of
OL,12,Fhighly televised events such as the
OL,13,FWorld Cup, to better protect those
OL,14,Fmost at risk."
OL,16,FBut the industry regulator, the
OL,17,FBetting and Gaming Council, said
OL,18,Fadvertising by licensed bookmakers had
OL,19,Fdeclined in the last five years,
OL,20,Fincluding during major football
OL,21,Ftournaments.
